Introduction

A-Daily was a girl group under DK Entertainment. They originally debuted as six on December 3, 2014 with their first single "If You Don't Tell Me".

Original members Yunseol, ChaeE, Jade and Diana left the group sometime during early 2015. Then shortly after new members, Jei and YoungBi joined the group. Now with the group having four members they released their second single "Spotlight." On August 3, 2016 the group released their first mini album Chu. On September 23, 2016 they, together with Haejeong released the theme song for "2016 K-Culture Korea Youth Performing Arts Festival". On January 10, 2017 the group released their third digital single "Snow World." In 2018 Jei and YoungBi left the group and were replaced by Taeryeong and NoA. Taeryeong left the group the same year.

The group is presumed to have disbanded sometime in 2019 due to inactivity.
